  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Factor the numerator",
      "content": "$$x^3 - 9x = x(x^2 - 9) = x(x-3)(x+3)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Factor the denominator",
      "content": "$$x^2 - 2x - 3 = (x-3)(x+1)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Cancel the common factor",
      "content": "Since $x>3$, $x-3\\neq0$, we can cancel: $$\\frac{x(x-3)(x+3)}{(x-3)(x+1)} = \\frac{x(x+3)}{x+1}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Identify the equivalent expression",
      "content": "The simplified form $\\frac{x(x+3)}{x+1}$ corresponds to choice D. <br/> That matches choice D \u2014 <strong>D</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
